column5: Scored this little lady this morning out in the bay       I had a smaller one come by for a nibble just minutes before she came to dance    http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wHo5MUN8mb8
you are now my hero.   good job keep it up!

Damn, wish I could have said the same for one I hooked 2 weeks ago in Keswick. Wish I would have landed her, was about the same size for sure. Watched her cruise by under our portable a few times then finally grabbed my minnow. snapped at the knot on one of those davidson perch rigs.  Nice catch man.
That was a cool shot of the fish taking the bait.  Sweet
Got ta love those gators Nicely documented
Nice pike  and nice video . what rig are you using? i thought i saw a red light blink on the bait? verry nice fish  what would you estimate the weight to be?
That was cool seeing that gator take the bait through the hole Congrats trophypikehunter and thansk for sharing Leechman
Now that was fun watching the bait disappearing into Mr Pike.  Nice fish too! Thanks for posting!!
Cool video and nice fish! thanks for sharing
great video, congrats
Well done.
Great video.  Thanks for sharing.  I loved the braided line scream as she ran!
Nice beastie.  Gotta love getting them like that, feeling the strike.
that was great!
Nice fat,clean pike. That was cool watching it hit the bait.
That was excellent.  It was fun watching the Pike suck in that bait.
wow awesome catch man, going to try and get something big this weekend!
Nice.
Cool watching them bite!
Awesome!!! Thanks

Thanks everybody!!   I make my own rig similar to the Quick Strike Rig except mine is a horizontal hold I call it the Dead Strike Rig.. The red light was the reflection from my camera and I would say that pike weighed between 7-10 pounds maybe..
nice!
